main event: Two unidentified objects were observed at a high speed, traveling from west to east, over the Naval Communications Station in Imperial Beach, California on November 9, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were observed for 1-2 minutes.
Radiosonde and pilot balloons were scheduled for launch from the nearby San Diego U.S. Navy weather station at 0702 that day.
One of the objects was reported to have hovered.
A separate report describes a large orange disk of light that was observed over Imperial Beach, California on November 16, 1952.
The orange disk of light was described as circular, about 20-25 feet in diameter and 1 foot thick, traveling at a very high rate of speed from south to north.
sighted object: two unidentified objects, a large orange disk of light
